javadoc:
Class for merging symbol changes. This class can merge non-conflicting symbol changes that were made to the checked out version. It can determine where there are conflicts between the latest checked in version and my checked out version. It can then manually merge the conflicting symbols.
Important: This class is intended to be used only for a single program version merge. It should be constructed and then merge() should be called on it. The merge() will perform an autoMerge() followed by mergeConflicts(). If symbols were automatically renamed due to conflicts, then a dialog will appear that shows this information to the user.

methods.name: resolveSymbolID
methods.comment:
Gets the symbolID from the result program that is the equivalent symbol
 to the symbol whose ID and program are specified as parameters.

params.name: pgm
params.comment: the program the symbol ID is coming from

params.name: symbolID
params.comment: the ID of the symbol in pgm

return.comment:
the ID of the corresponding symbol in the result program
 or -1 if there is no corresponding symbol in the result program.

methods.name: resolveNamespace
methods.comment:
This method allows other listing merge managers to resolve a namespace
 via the symbol merge manager. This is because the symbol merge manager
 actually merges namespaces and best knows how to resolve them.
 It also keeps track of how they have been resolved.

params.name: srcProgram
params.comment: the program version that the namespace to be resolved is coming from.

params.name: srcNamespace
params.comment: the namespace to be resolved

throws.comment:
if the name space can't be resolved due
 to a name conflict that can't be dealt with.

if the name space is not validly named
 for the result program.

return.comment: the namespace from the result program version

methods.name: createNamespace
methods.comment:
Get/create a uniquely named namespace. If the namespace's name can't
 be created because of a name conflict, it will be given a new conflict name.

params.name: resultProgram
params.comment: the program where the namespace is to be found or created

params.name: name
params.comment: the desired name for the namespace

params.name: st
params.comment: the symbol type for this namespace

params.name: resultAddr
params.comment: the address in the result program for this namespace

params.name: resultParentNs
params.comment: the parent of this namespace in the result program

throws.comment:
if the namespace couldn't be created
 because of an unresolvable name conflict.

if the namespace couldn't be created
 because of an invalid name.

return.comment: an equivalent namespace that exists or was created.

methods.name: setupSymbolChanges
methods.comment:
Determine the type of changes to the symbols in the LATEST and MY (CheckedOut) program.
 Changes can be symbol removed, added, changed, renamed, and set to primary.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: task monitor for displaying progress to the user

throws.comment: if the user cancels the merge.

methods.name: hasSymbolWithNameConflict
methods.comment:
Checks to see if there is a symbol in the otherProgram that conflicts
 with the indicated symbol. A conflict can be one of these types:
 1) a symbol other than label or function that has the same name and 
 namespace as another non label or function.
 2) a symbol at the same address with the same name and namespace.

params.name: program
params.comment: the program that contains the specified symbol

params.name: symbol
params.comment: the symbol (Can be original, latest, or my.)

params.name: otherProgram
params.comment: the program to be checked for a conflicting symbol

params.name: saveConflict
params.comment:
if true this will also save the conflict for processing or in
 some cases automatically process the conflict.

return.comment: true if there is a symbol name conflict

methods.name: renameSymbol
methods.comment: Renames the oldSymbol to have a name and namespace equivalent to that of the newSymbol.

params.name: oldProgram
params.comment: the program containing the old symbol

params.name: oldSymbol
params.comment: the old symbol

params.name: newProgram
params.comment: the program containing the new symbol

params.name: newSymbol
params.comment: the new symbol

methods.name: getPath
methods.comment:
Gets an array of strings indicating what the full path  would be if a symbol with

params.name: name
params.comment: the symbol name

params.name: namespace
params.comment: the namespace

methods.name: setPrimary
methods.comment:

params.name: addr
params.comment: the address

params.name: conflictOption
params.comment: KEEP_LATEST, KEEP_MY, or KEEP_ORIGINAL.
